        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 2000, 4000, 8000, and 9000 models with steel fuel tanks built between
                    November, 1995 and June 4, 1998. These models may have the wrong gasket material under the fuel
                    sender and/or the fuel sender opening cover plate. The correct gasket material is a combination of
                    cork and rubber. The gasket which may have been used is made of only rubber and is breaking apart
                    and entering the fuel system, resulting in pieces getting lodged in fuel lines and filler. Fuel
                    seepage at the fuel tank sender/cover plate is another indicator the gasket is failing.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
