        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the gasket at the fuel tank sender and the cover plate. If the rubber gasket
                    material is a red color, the gasket must be changed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel tank sender or cover plate and inspect for signs of deterioration. It
                    may be necessary to flush the fuel tank and fuel system to remove particles of gasket material.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Do not drain fuel near an open flame or intense heat. To do so is a dangerous practice which
                        could create a hazardous work area. This could lead to personal injury and/or property damage.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new gasket Part Number 464751C3 on fuel tank sender and/or cover plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the mounting screws. Tighten the screws to 35 to 60 in-lbs (4 to 7 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
